      After an Upstash failure, checkRateLimit still attempts distributed.limit(identifier)
      on every request before falling back to memory, so the advertised graceful fallback
      continues to pay the dead-network failure path repeatedly.
    recommendation: "Clear or bypass the Redis-backed limiter after failure for a cooldown period before retrying it."
